item.title: 1. Install minimal
item.description:
https://download.rockylinux.org/pub/rocky/9/isos/x86_64/Rocky-9.2-x86_64-minimal.iso
After the minimal install, login using root user/password and Update stuff:
dnf update -y Copy
enable ssh so you can copy paste stuff:
systemctl start sshd Copy
systemctl enable sshd Copy
enable ssh for root:
# Open the ssh config file: nano /etc/ssh/ssh_config # Add this line: PermitRootLogin Yes Copy
systemctl restart sshd Copy
View Status of ssh:
systemctl status sshd Copy

Install VPN (tailscale in this case):
curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh Copy
follow the instructions for the vpn install

install this GUI:
sudo dnf groupinstall "Server with GUI" -y Copy
Change the default boot to graphical mode:
sudo systemctl set-default graphical.target Copy
sudo reboot Copy

Install xrdp (Remote Desktop):
sudo dnf install epel-release -y Copy
sudo dnf install xrdp -y Copy
sudo systemctl start xrdp Copy
sudo systemctl enable xrdp Copy
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3389/tcp Copy
sudo firewall-cmd --reload Copy
sudo reboot Copy

If the sound is not working run this command and reboot
sudo dnf install alsa-sof-firmware.noarch Copy


https://flathub.org/
sudo dnf install flatpak Copy
sudo flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://dl.flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo Copy
sudo reboot Copy


sudo dnf install epel-release sudo dnf upgrade sudo reboot Copy
sudo dnf config-manager --add-repo http://developer.download.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/repos/rhel9/$(uname -i)/cuda-rhel9.repo sudo dnf install kernel-headers-$(uname -r) kernel-devel-$(uname -r) tar bzip2 make automake gcc gcc-c++ pciutils elfutils-libelf-devel libglvnd-opengl libglvnd-glx libglvnd-devel acpid pkgconfig dkms sudo dnf module install nvidia-driver:latest-dkms echo "blacklist nouveau" | sudo tee /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist-nouveau.conf echo 'omit_drivers+=" nouveau "' | sudo tee /etc/dracut.conf.d/blacklist-nouveau.conf sudo dracut --regenerate-all --force sudo depmod -a Copy
sudo reboot Copy
After reboot, check the nvidia drivers install:
nvidia-smi Copy
You should see something like this, and you're good:
+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ | NVIDIA-SMI 545.23.06 Driver Version: 545.23.06 CUDA Version: 12.3 | |-----------------------------------------+----------------------+----------------------+ | GPU Name Persistence-M | Bus-Id Disp.A | Volatile Uncorr. ECC | | Fan Temp Perf Pwr:Usage/Cap | Memory-Usage | GPU-Util Compute M. | | | | MIG M. | |=========================================+======================+======================| | 0 NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090 Off | 00000000:00:10.0 On | Off | | 31% 25C P8 33W / 450W | 231MiB / 24564MiB | 0% Default | | | | N/A | +-----------------------------------------+----------------------+----------------------+ +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ | Processes: | | GPU GI CI PID Type Process name GPU Memory | | ID ID Usage | |=======================================================================================| | 0 N/A N/A 2476 G /usr/libexec/Xorg 200MiB | | 0 N/A N/A 2833 G /usr/bin/gnome-shell 18MiB | +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ Copy


Download and install houdini from the sidefx website & follow the instructions in the terminal
Things that sidefx fails to mention in order to get houdini to run:
sudo dnf install python3-qt5 Copy
sudo dnf install libXScrnSaver-devel-1.2.3-10.el9. Copy
sudo dnf install libnsl Copy
sudo reboot Copy


sudo dnf config-manager --add-repo=https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo Copy
sudo dnf install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io Copy
Start and enable Docker to run on system boot:
sudo systemctl enable --now docker Copy
Once the Docker is in place, it is now time to deploy Portainer on Rocky Linux.


To begin with, you need to create Portainer server data volume. Please note that Portainer requires persistent storage in order to maintain the database and configuration information it needs to function:
sudo docker volume create portainer_data Copy
The volume should be created in somewhere like :
"/var/lib/docker/volumes/portainer_data/_data"
sudo docker volume inspect portainer_data Copy
install portainer into that volume:
sudo docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -p 9443:9443 --name portainer \ --restart=always -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \ -v portainer_data:/data portainer/portainer-ce:latest Copy
To access Portainer server UI, then navigate to the browser and enter the address:
https://localhost:9443/
